cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.NI 

This paper deals with the analysis of networks and their stability in the presence of noise. It uses centrality measures and local connections to understand the stability of the network. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
